import React, { useState } from 'react'; const MyBookings = () => { const [state, updateState] = useState({ username:"", type:"", checkIn:"", checkOut:"", persons:"", children:"" }) useEffect(() => { if(localStorage.getItem("signupData")){ let username=JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem("signupData")).username let type="two-bedroom" let checkIn="26/10/2020" let checkOut="27/10/2020" let persons="3" let children="1" updateState({ username:username, type:type, checkIn:checkIn, checkOut:checkOut, persons:persons, children:children }) } }, []) return (
